sen.khyber.apcs.superArray

Class SuperIntArray

  • Object
    • MyArrayList<Integer>
      • SuperIntArray
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Integer>, Collection<Integer>, List<Integer>

    public class SuperIntArray
extends MyArrayList<Integer>
    more closely implements our in-class SuperIntArray, because it extends MyArrayList The one method that isn't the same after autoboxing is toArray(), because it returns an Integer[] instead of an int[], and due to Java's insufficient autoboxing, generic type erasure, and lack of true value types, it is impossible to write. Therefore, I wrote a toIntArray() method that returns an int[]
    Author:
    Khyber Sen
    See Also:
    toIntArray()
